      "body" : "From how I read it the assertion will never panic, but I agree this should be a nullcheck branch. \r\n\r\nI see the two calls to `MarkBlockAsReceived(..)` which exclude the final param, on lines [2260](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/3908fc4728059719bed0e1c7b1c8b388c2d4a8da/src/net_processing.cpp#L2260) and [3192](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/3908fc4728059719bed0e1c7b1c8b388c2d4a8da/src/net_processing.cpp#L3129). Both are protected by `cs_main`. The former [will only retrieve blocks not marked in flight](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/3908fc4728059719bed0e1c7b1c8b388c2d4a8da/src/net_processing.cpp#L2235) and the latter uses `FindNextBlocksToDownload(..)`, which itself [only provides blocks not marked as in flight](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/3908fc4728059719bed0e1c7b1c8b388c2d4a8da/src/net_processing.cpp#L529). So the assertion's branch will never be exercised in these two cases.",
